The paper focuses on the development of a framework and resources for a real-life scenario involving an assistive bathing robot for elderly subjects. The paper discusses the use of audio and RGB-D visual streams for multimodal learning and recognition, which falls under the categories of robotics (cs.RO), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), computer vision (cs.CV), signal processing (cs.SD), and multimedia (cs.MM).
